description.narrative: 3.1. By 2020, health managers have increased capacity to implement evidence-based and equity focused district health system strengthening plans, including in emergency, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Micronutrients, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 3.By 2020 mothers and children, especially the most vulnerable , have access to quality healthcare services (individual and population based), including in emergency
